  <div xmlns:v="http://rdf.data-vocabulary.org/#" typeof="v:Review">
    <div class="main review-item" id="4658447">
        

  <header class="main-hd">
    <h3 class="title">
      <a href="https://book.douban.com/review/4658447/" class="title-link">导论性著作的任务</a>
      <div class="toggle_review right">        <a href="javascript:;" id="toggle-4658447"class="indicator unfold j" title="展开全文">        </a>
      </div>
    </h3>
    

<div class="header-more">
    <a class="author-avatar" href="https://www.douban.com/people/48152289/"><img width="48" height="48" src="https://img3.doubanio.com/icon/u48152289-2.jpg"></a>
    <a href="https://www.douban.com/people/48152289/" class="author">
      <span property="v:reviewer">48545362</span>
    </a>    <span property="v:rating" class="allstar50 main-title-rating" title="力荐"></span>
  <span property="v:dtreviewed" content="2011-02-20"
      class="main-meta">2011-02-20 13:39:48</span>
</div>

  </header>

        <div class="main-bd">
          <div id="review_4658447_short" class="review-short">
            <div class="short-content">
                     作为一本导论性著作 重要的 不是去急于深化知识，而是详尽而客观的介绍与陈述。毕竟现今的政治哲学内部中 总还有那么多的不确定性，还有那么多未知有待发掘。任何的倾向性，哪怕是再小的引导与暗示 都极易助长武断的偏见。所以作为一本入门导读作品 作者也需要法官的公正 中...

